theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- From `P1`, we have `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
    have h₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
    -- Hence `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
    have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := closure_mono h₁
    -- And `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
    -- thanks to monotonicity lemmas.
    have h₃ :
        closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_closure (A := A)
    exact Set.Subset.trans h₂ h₃
  ·
    -- The interior of `closure A` is contained in `closure A`.
    have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono h

import Mathlib
import Aesop

namespace Topology

variable {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]

theorem closure_subset_closure_interior_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  -- From `P1`, we know `closure A = closure (interior A)`.
  have hEq : closure A = closure (interior A) :=
    Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1 (A := A) hP1
  -- Rewrite the goal using this equality; reflexivity then finishes the proof.
  simpa [hEq] using
    (subset_rfl : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior A))

theorem closure_interior_closure_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure A := by
  -- Apply `closure_minimal` to the inclusion
  -- `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A`, using the fact that `closure A`
  -- is a closed set.
  exact
    closure_minimal
      (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A)
      isClosed_closure

theorem closure_inter_subset_closures
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  have hA : closure (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)
  have hB : closure (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ closure B :=
    closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)
  exact ⟨hA hx, hB hx⟩
